The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Afghan blast 

 Kandahar, Jan. 16 (Reuters): Bombers killed at least 26 people in two separate attacks in southern Afghanistan today, a day after a Canadian diplomat and two civilians were killed in the area. 

 At least 20 people died when a bomb attached to a motorcycle exploded at a playground where hundreds of people had gathered for a festival in Spin Boldak, bordering Pakistan. 

 Turkey flu 

 Istanbul (Reuters): Turkeys health ministry said on Monday that a fourth person had died of the bird flu virus that has swept the country over the past two weeks, state-run Anatolian news agency reported. 

 Lanka deaths 

 Colombo (Reuters): Two men were shot dead in eastern Sri Lanka on Monday in violence ahead of visits by US and Norwegian envoys trying to halt a slide back to civil war. 

 Bangla court 

 Dhaka (Reuters): A Bangladesh court has sentenced a member of an outlawed Islamist group to 15 years in prison for involvement in serial bomb attacks across the country in August. 




